Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil. Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(finely chopped) (stalks and all). Lay one @British chicken breasts{2} on a #chopping board{}, place your hand flat on top and slice into it from the side (being careful not to slice all the way through). Open it up like a book. Repeat for the other breasts.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

In a #small bowl{}, mix the parsley, @flaked almonds{15}, half the @wholegrain mustard{1}(divided) and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Lay the butterflied chicken out flat on a large #baking tray{}, season with salt and pepper then spread the @mayonnaise{1} over each breast. Cover with the almond mix. Press down to make sure it sticks to the chicken. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Place the @broccoli florets{200} on a lined baking tray. Drizzle with a little @oil{a drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} and place on the middle shelf of your oven. Cook for ~{15-18%minutes}. Meanwhile, peel and chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks. Add the potato to the pan of boiling water and cook until tender, ~{15%minutes}.

> TIP: The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

When cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the saucepan, off the heat.

Mash the cooked sweet potato with the remaining mustard and a good pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} using a #potato masher{}. Taste to check for seasoning, then divide between the plates.

Remove the chicken and broccoli from the oven, and place the chicken on top of the mash, with a portion of roasted broccoli alongside.

Tuck in and enjoy!